Package hms.utils

Class Timeslot

Object
Timeslot
public class Timeslot extends Object
Represents a timeslot with a start time and an end time.

    • sdf

      private static final SimpleDateFormat sdf
      The date format used for parsing and formatting timeslot strings with the format is "dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss".

      This format will be used for the toString(), getStartTimeString() and getEndTimeString() methods.

    • Timeslot

      public Timeslot(String timeslotString)
      Constructs a Timeslot object from a String, the String format must follow the same format as the toString() method of this class.

      This acts as a parsing method for the timeslot as well.

      Parameters:
      timeslotString - A string representation of the timeslot
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the timeslot string is null or has an invalid format
      See Also:
      • toString()

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns a string representation of the timeslot. The format is "dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss - dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss".

      This acts as a serialization method for the timeslot too.
